âœ… 1. Class Naming Convention

Use PascalCase (Every word starts with a capital letter)

Name should be noun (represents an object/entity)

Examples:

Employee
StudentDetails
OrderController

âœ… 2. Variable Naming Convention

Use camelCase (first letter small, inner words capital)

Name should be a noun

It should be meaningful

Examples:

int employeeId;
String firstName;
double totalAmount;

âœ… 3. Method Naming Convention

Use camelCase

Name should be a verb (because methods perform action)

Examples:

void calculateSalary()
String getEmployeeName()
boolean isValidUser()

âœ… 4. Interface Naming Convention

Use PascalCase

Name should represent capabilities or behavior

Often ends with -able or -ible (not mandatory)

Examples:

Runnable
Serializable
PaymentService
DatabaseOperations

âœ… 5. Enum Naming Convention
ðŸ”¹ Enum Name

Use PascalCase

enum Color { ... }
enum StatusType { ... }

ðŸ”¹ Enum Constants

Use ALL_CAPS with underscores

Examples:

enum Status {
    ACTIVE,
    INACTIVE,
    PENDING,
    FAILED
}

âœ… 6. Package Naming Convention

(Adding this because it's often asked)

Use lowercase

Usually reverse domain name

Examples:

com.company.project
org.example.app.service

ðŸ”¥ Interview-Ready One-Liner Summary
Element	          Convention	        Example
Class	          PascalCase	        EmployeeDetails
Variable	      camelCase	            totalAmount
Method	          camelCase (verb)	    calculateSalary()
Interface	      PascalCase	        Runnable, PaymentService
Enum Name	      PascalCase	        StatusType
Enum Constants	  ALL_CAPS	            ACTIVE, FAILED
Package	          lowercase	            com.example.service
